       title="Manage Users" id="Manage-Users">

    <chapter title="Overview" id="overview">
        <p>
            This section describes how Manage Users within RBAM.
        </p>
        <p>
            Managing Users consists of assigning and revoking Roles to/from users.
            The Users are defined elsewhere in the application.
        </p>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Users" id="users">
        <p>
            On the RBAM home page, click the <emphasis>Manage Users</emphasis> button.
            A paged list of users is displayed showing the number of Roles and Permissions for each user.
        </p>
        <p>
            To view the details for a user, click the <emphasis>View</emphasis> button.
        </p>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="User" id="user">
        <p>
            The user page shows the Roles assigned to a user, Roles not currently assigned, and Permission that Role
            assignments grant.
        </p>
        <p>
            A user can be assigned a Role directly or indirectly; an indirectly assigned Role is a descendant of
            a directly assigned Role.
        </p>
        <p>
            Roles can be assigned to and revoked from the user; Roles can be revoked individually or all Roles
            can be revoked.
        </p>
        <note>
            <p>
                Indirectly assigned Roles can not be individually revoked.
            </p>
            <p>
                To revoke an indirectly assigned role the directly assigned ancestor Role must be revoked, or the
                indirectly assigned Role removed from the directly assigned Role's hierarchy.
            </p>
        </note>

        <chapter title="Assign a Role" id="assign-a-role">
            <p>
                To assign a Role to a user, click Assign button for an unassigned Role.
                The user will be directly assigned this Role and indirectly assigned any descendant Roles,
                and granted Permissions associated with all the assigned Roles.
            </p>
            <p>
                The page will show the users new Role assignment(s) and Permissions.
            </p>
        </chapter>

        <chapter title="Revoke a Role" id="revoke-a-role">
            <p>
                To revoke a Role from a user, click the Revoke button for an assigned Role.
                The Role and any descendant Roles will be revoked,
                as will Permissions associated with all the revoked Roles.
            </p>
            <p>
                The page will show the users new Role assignment(s) and Permissions.
            </p>
        </chapter>

        <chapter title="Revoke all Roles" id="revoke-all-roles">
            <p>
                Click the Revoke All button. All Roles and Permissions will be revoked.
            </p>
            <p>
                The page will show the users new Role assignment(s) and Permissions.
            </p>
        </chapter>
    </chapter>

